tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated HbA1c, indicating impaired glucose regulation or possible prediabetes, and a slightly increased creatinine, which may suggest early renal impairment. All other parameters are within normal limits. Recommend clinical correlation for diabetes risk and assessment of renal function, with follow-up as appropriate.
